Peter Gyenes has four decades of experience in global technical, sales, marketing, and general management positions in the high tech sector.
He is currently on the board of Sophos, a global security software company.
He served as Chairman and CEO of Ascential Software until its acquisition by IBM in April 2005.
Peter serves on several corporate boards, including VistaPrint, Netezza Corporation and Pegasystems Inc.
Previously, he was President and CEO of Racal InterLan, Inc., and in executive positions at Data General Corporation, Encore Computer Corporation and Prime Computer, Inc.
Peter is a Trustee Emeritus of the Massachusetts Technology Leadership Council and holds a Bachelor of Mathematics and an MBA from Columbia University.



